article.headline: Bradley 73, Detroit 65
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Andrew Warren scored 24 points and made four of Bradley's five 3-pointers in a 73-65 victory over Detroit on Wednesday night. Warren exceeded his average of 18.2 by sinking 5 of 11 shots, including 4 of 8 3-pointers, and all 10 free throws. Dodie Dunson added 18 points and Will Egolf 11 for the Braves (6-5), who won their second in a row. Ray McCallum scored 15 points and had a game-high nine assists to lead the Titans (7-6). Eli Holman added 14 points and Chris Blake 11. Bradley led 35-26 at halftime, and the lead peaked at 38-26 when Warren opened the second half with a 3-pointer with 18:57 to go. But the Titans chipped away, finally tying it 59-59 on Holman's jumper with 5:02 left. Bradley responded with a 9-1 run for a 68-60 lead with 36 seconds to go, and that sealed it.
